  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic adversarial UoA for ASME V&V 40 COU2 (VAD hemolysis, MRL 5). The package presents a plausible credibility assessment for CFD-predicted absolute hemolysis in a Class III centrifugal VAD. The targeted weakness W-AR-05 is embedded in the Output Comparison validation result: one validation result omits the comparedAgainst link entirely, while the narrative describes a well-regarded experimental dataset in positive terms. A second validation result carries a comparedAgainst link to a dataset collected at 3 L/min / 3000 RPM (low-shear regime), whereas the COU demands predictions across 4–6 L/min / 4500–6000 RPM operating points where shear-induced hemolysis mechanisms differ substantially. The mismatch is plausibly deniable because the comparator geometry is identical (FDA generic centrifugal pump) and the scalar hemolysis index values overlap numerically, obscuring the regime difference on a quick read.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-predicts-absolute-hemolyis-vad-cou2",
