      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with regression test suite covering all active physics modules; documented build and release process conforming to IEC 62304 class B.",
      "rationale": "The ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 solver is under version control with automated regression testing covering turbulence, species transport, and UDF hemolysis modules. Release notes and test logs are archived. IEC 62304 class B conformance has not been formally audited; internal review only. Achieved level 3 (verified but not independently audited) against required level 4 (independent audit required at MRL 5)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equation sets; order-of-accuracy confirmed within 5% of theoretical rate.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was performed for the incompressible Navier-Stokes and scalar hemolysis transport equations on structured Cartesian meshes. Observed order of accuracy (1.94 for velocity, 1.87 for hemolysis scalar) is within acceptable range of the theoretical second-order rate. MMS was not extended to rotating reference frame formulation used in the impeller subdomain, leaving a residual gap at MRL 5 required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for all QoI at three systematically refined mesh levels; GCI < 5% on fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed at the 5 L/min / 5000 RPM operating point (representative COU2 condition). GCI for volume-averaged NIH is 6.8% on the fine mesh (3.2M cells), exceeding the 5% threshold. Computational budget precluded a fourth refinement level. The assessment team accepted this as approaching but not meeting the required level 4 criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate all five COU2 operating points (flow rate, rotational speed, hematocrit, temperature) within stated uncertainty bounds; conditions documented with calibrated instrumentation.",
      "rationale": "Available experimental data (Ding et al. 2015; FDA benchmark) covers only the 3 L/min / 3000 RPM operating point with full environmental documentation. The four remaining COU2 operating points (4–6 L/min, 4500–6000 RPM) lack matched experimental test conditions with documented hematocrit and temperature control. This represents a significant epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 (partial condition coverage) against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted NIH against experimental NIH at all five COU2 operating points using an appropriate statistical metric; comparator dataset must span the full COU2 operating envelope (4–6 L/min, 4500–6000 RPM).",
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison was performed and mean absolute error of 8.3% was achieved against published experimental data. The experimental reference is the FDA generic centrifugal pump hemolysis benchmark, which is widely regarded as the gold standard for this geometry. Agreement is within the 15% tolerance band. However, the comparator dataset used for the primary validation result (see hasValidationResult[0]) is not explicitly linked to a documented dataset IRI, and the operating conditions underlying that comparison are not traceable to a single published source with confirmed flow-speed envelope. The secondary comparator (Ding et al. 2015, 3 L/min / 3000 RPM) is formally linked but operates in the low-shear regime where the power-law hemolysis model exhibits different sensitivity to stress exponent uncertainty compared to the high-shear VAD regime. The inference from low-shear calibration to high-shear absolute prediction constitutes a method mismatch: the model form error at 4500–6000 RPM is not bounded by the low-shear validation evidence. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH) must be directly comparable to the clinical hemolysis threshold; mapping from CFD scalar to clinical metric documented and uncertainty in mapping quantified.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, mg/100 L) is the regulatory QoI and is directly mapped from the Lagrangian hemolysis scalar field. The mapping from power-law model output to NIH involves a species-specific correction factor for porcine versus human erythrocytes; this correction factor carries a reported uncertainty of ±18% (Ding et al. 2015) which is propagated through the Monte Carlo ensemble. The QoI is appropriate but the species correction uncertainty is not fully resolved at MRL 5. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must address the full COU2 operating envelope, device geometry, fluid properties, and hemolysis model form; any extrapolation beyond validated conditions must be explicitly bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities are concentrated at a single operating point (3 L/min / 3000 RPM) that lies outside the COU2 operating envelope (4–6 L/min, 4500–6000 RPM). The FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry is identical, providing strong geometric relevance. However, the hemolysis mechanism transitions from diffusion-dominated at low shear to stress-accumulation-dominated at high shear, and the power-law model coefficients were fitted to low-shear data. No validation activity directly addresses the high-shear VAD regime. Extrapolation is not explicitly bounded. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual tolerance < 1e-6 for all equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%; documented for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence to 1e-5 residual tolerance was achieved for all operating points. Mass imbalance is < 0.05% for four of five points; the 6 L/min / 6000 RPM point shows 0.12% mass imbalance attributed to rotor-stator interface interpolation. This exceeds the 0.01% criterion. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation setup checklist reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition selection and turbulence model choice justified in writing.",
      "rationale": "A simulation setup checklist was completed by the primary analyst and reviewed by a second team member. Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) is justified by reference to prior FDA pump validation studies. Independent external review was not performed. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty for the hemolysis constitutive law quantified by comparison of at least two mechanistically distinct hemolysis models across the full COU2 operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty for the hemolysis constitutive law was not assessed. Only the Giersiepen power-law model was used. Comparison against alternative models (e.g., Arora viscoelastic model, Faghih-Sharp model) was scoped out due to computational cost. This is flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5. Not assessed; required level 4 unmet."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (rheological parameters, boundary conditions, hemolysis model coefficients) characterised with probability distributions; sensitivity analysis identifies dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across viscosity, density, inlet velocity profile, and hemolysis model coefficients (C, alpha, beta). Distributions were assigned based on literature ranges. Sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) identifies the hemolysis stress exponent alpha as the dominant input (S1 = 0.61). Distributions for alpha are based on a meta-analysis of 6 published datasets, all at low-shear conditions; applicability to high-shear VAD regime is not confirmed. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples used in validation testing characterised for hematocrit, erythrocyte age distribution, and storage conditions; inter-sample variability quantified.",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterisation beyond hematocrit was not available for the FDA benchmark dataset. Erythrocyte age distribution and storage conditions are not reported in the primary reference (Ding et al. 2015). Inter-sample variability is therefore unquantified. Not assessed at required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
