    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the CFD hemolysis prediction capability for COU2 on the basis of the quantitative output comparison result (mean absolute error 8.3%, within the 15% tolerance band) and the strong geometric fidelity of the validation configuration to the COU device. The team noted that the experimental benchmark is widely regarded as the most rigorous publicly available dataset for the FDA generic centrifugal pump and that agreement at the documented operating point is well within acceptable bounds. Multiple credibility factor gaps were acknowledged but judged collectively insufficient to overturn the positive quantitative evidence. The absence of a formally linked comparator dataset for the primary validation result and the operating-regime mismatch between the secondary comparator (3 L/min / 3000 RPM) and the COU2 envelope (4–6 L/min, 4500–6000 RPM) were noted as limitations but not treated as disqualifying given the geometric and scalar-metric overlap. Decision: Accepted.",
